- No, he'll be an Italian.

603
00:50:06,932 --> 00:50:08,524
Answer the phone!

604
00:50:12,504 --> 00:50:13,937
Hello?

605
00:50:14,206 --> 00:50:15,639
No, he's not in.

606
00:50:16,174 --> 00:50:18,199
Very well, I'll tell him.

607
00:50:18,310 --> 00:50:20,972
He said he'd call back this afternoon.

608
00:50:21,513 --> 00:50:23,481
Funny name, Manganiello.

609
00:51:25,944 --> 00:51:28,606
- Yes, what is it?
- I'm <i>Monsieur</i> Clerici.

610
00:51:28,713 --> 00:51:32,877
- You've got the wrong apartment.
- I've an appointment.

611
00:51:32,984 --> 00:51:34,178
You're Italian?

612
00:51:34,286 --> 00:51:37,346
The professor is expecting them.
I'll take care.

613
00:51:45,563 --> 00:51:46,996
Get away, Marcello!

614
00:51:50,669 --> 00:51:54,298
He'll bite you! Run!

615
00:52:00,912 --> 00:52:02,311
Down, Roby!

616
00:52:03,014 --> 00:52:05,005
Get down! Sit down!

617
00:52:14,492 --> 00:52:16,983
You're <i>Monsieur</i> Clerici, aren't you?

618
00:52:17,562 --> 00:52:18,790
Come in.

619
00:52:23,101 --> 00:52:26,593
- Nothing to be afraid of.
- Me? I'm not a bit frightened.

620
00:52:26,705 --> 00:52:29,936
Well then come up.
He won't bite now, I tell you.

621
00:52:30,308 --> 00:52:32,640
Funny, usually dogs like me.

622
00:52:36,815 --> 00:52:38,976
Is this the first time
