742
01:00:06,764 --> 01:00:10,894
- Why are you so hostile?
- Because I'm sincere.

743
01:00:14,505 --> 01:00:16,473
Over here she had a scar.

744
01:00:20,144 --> 01:00:24,547
No! No! Let me go!

745
01:01:25,309 --> 01:01:27,072
Who knows what it's for?

746
01:01:27,178 --> 01:01:29,078
But it isn't gold the way I imagined.

747
01:01:29,180 --> 01:01:32,274
From here it's almost as small
as the one I have on my night table.

748
01:01:32,383 --> 01:01:33,941
They say at least once a month,

749
01:01:34,051 --> 01:01:37,452
some disappointed lover
throws himself off. How stupid.

750
01:01:38,155 --> 01:01:40,919
- You want to go to the Tower?
- Yes.

751
01:01:47,164 --> 01:01:48,222
Taxi!

752
01:01:48,332 --> 01:01:52,029
Yes. I'm glad we're going up
the Eiffel Tower.

753
01:02:01,245 --> 01:02:04,043
Quick! To the Eiffel Tower. <i>Ciao!</i>

754
01:02:04,982 --> 01:02:07,576
And you?

755
01:02:20,665 --> 01:02:21,996
Attention!

756
01:02:22,733 --> 01:02:25,566
Now, supple. Go on. Hup!

757
01:02:27,338 --> 01:02:29,101
Helene dear, chin up.

758
01:02:32,109 --> 01:02:33,167
Hup!

759
01:02:35,246 --> 01:02:36,873
Try it again now.

760
01:02:40,718 --> 01:02:43,152
Watch your knees, Denise.

761
01:02:44,622 --> 01:02:46,112
Take a breath.

762
01:02:50,428 --> 01:02:53,124
That's starting to look good, isn't it?

763
01:02:57,735 --> 01:02:59,032
Your head.

764
01:03:04,475 --> 01:03:06,033
Your points out.

765
01:03:07,345 --> 01:03:09,040
Eyes still, Margot.

766
01:03:21,592 --> 01:03:23,025
Take a break.

767
01:03:26,130 --> 01:03:27,791
Thank you, madame.

768
01:03:35,806 --> 01:03:38,206
- Is there some place to talk?
- Here.

769
01:03:38,309 --> 01:03:40,209
- No, not here.
- Why not?

770
01:03:52,390 --> 01:03:54,620
I have some friends in Brazil.

771
01:03:54,892 --> 01:03:57,690
I'll leave everything if you come with me.

772
01:03:59,163 --> 01:04:02,132
I, on the other hand,
have friends in Italy.

773
01:04:02,233 --> 01:04:04,428
I received a letter. Read it.

774
01:04:08,339 --> 01:04:12,742
"If you ever get this letter,
it will be in spite of the prison censors."

775
01:04:13,444 --> 01:04:16,811
You must never make the gesture
as wide as this.

776
01:04:18,616 --> 01:04:20,584
Why did you stop? Go on.

777
01:04:23,487 --> 01:04:25,978
"They come suddenly in the night
and kick the door of my cell

778
01:04:26,090 --> 01:04:28,183
"so as not to let me sleep."

779
01:04:29,660 --> 01:04:31,594
- Why do...
- Continue.

780
01:04:31,695 --> 01:04:34,095
Why do you make me read this letter?

781
01:04:34,198 --> 01:04:36,063
I'll tell you in a bit.

782
01:04:37,735 --> 01:04:40,636
"Some days,
there are the false executions.

783
01:04:41,705 --> 01:04:44,435
"They sent me the priest
three times already

784
01:04:44,542 --> 01:04:47,067
"and I refused extreme unction.

785
01:04:47,178 --> 01:04:49,544
"They gave me castor oil again,
but they should realize

786
01:04:49,647 --> 01:04:51,740
"that after almost 20 years,

787
01:04:52,583 --> 01:04:55,074
"I'm used to it. It has no effect."

788
01:04:56,053 --> 01:04:57,953
Why must I read this letter?

789
01:04:58,055 --> 01:05:00,148
You want me to tell you?

790
01:05:00,257 --> 01:05:02,589
Because you're a Fascist! A spy!

791
01:05:03,194 --> 01:05:06,095
You imagine you took us in?
You're mistaken.

792
01:05:08,466 --> 01:05:09,899
Does your husband know?

793
01:05:10,000 --> 01:05:12,264
Why do you think you were received?

794
01:05:13,804 --> 01:05:15,237
You're only a worm.

795
01:05:15,339 --> 01:05:17,739
You revolt me! You're disgusting!

796
01:05:19,710 --> 01:05:22,042
I'm getting Giulia at the hotel.

797
01:05:22,146 --> 01:05:24,137
We'll be on the first train home.

798
01:05:24,248 --> 01:05:27,274
You'd never do it.
You're too much of a coward.

799
01:05:52,810 --> 01:05:54,744
Marcello! Hold me.

800
01:06:05,489 --> 01:06:07,457
Marcello, I'm frightened.

801
01:06:10,094 --> 01:06:12,392
Marcello, please don't hurt us.

802
01:06:16,967 --> 01:06:19,458
Swear it! Swear it, please.

803
01:06:20,538 --> 01:06:21,971
I don't know.

804
01:07:05,282 --> 01:07:07,045
Giulia, look at this.

805
01:07:14,058 --> 01:07:15,787
Anna! Come here!

806
01:07:18,295 --> 01:07:19,853
It's a surprise!

807
01:07:22,566 --> 01:07:26,002
Look at that color. It's a dream!

808
01:07:26,103 --> 01:07:28,833
Come and look at this one. Here.

809
01:07:32,343 --> 01:07:35,141
Anna! It's divine!

810
01:07:37,381 --> 01:07:39,872
Look how beautiful it is! Just look!

811
01:07:42,519 --> 01:07:44,077
Giulia, come on.

812
01:08:00,137 --> 01:08:03,231
It's very big, all in wood,
with enormous beds.

813
01:08:03,607 --> 01:08:05,006
The house belonged to my grandfather.

814
01:08:05,109 --> 01:08:07,202
Luca and I used to go there often.

815
01:08:07,311 --> 01:08:08,801
Roby, here!

816
01:08:08,912 --> 01:08:12,871
But now with what's going on in Spain,
we don't leave Paris any longer.

817
01:08:12,983 --> 01:08:15,747
All right, Roby! That's enough!
Come here!

818
01:08:16,053 --> 01:08:18,817
La Savoie is beautiful.
I can't wait to get back.

819
01:08:36,507 --> 01:08:40,534
<i>Dottore! Dottore!</i>

820
01:08:41,211 --> 01:08:43,839
Come on, I know you're back there.

821
01:08:43,947 --> 01:08:46,438
Why don't you want to see me?

822
01:08:46,550 --> 01:08:48,745
I've been running after you all day.

823
01:08:48,852 --> 01:08:51,548
And it's freezing here.

824
01:08:54,792 --> 01:08:57,590
You ought to come out
and have a chat now.

825
01:08:59,129 --> 01:09:01,563
What is it you're worrying about?

826
01:09:01,999 --> 01:09:05,025
We'll go somewhere inside.
We'll talk about it.

827
01:09:06,704 --> 01:09:08,672
I have my job, you know.

828
01:09:09,973 --> 01:09:11,702
The time's passing.

829
01:09:14,244 --> 01:09:18,408
You must have a plan by now.

830
01:09:18,782 --> 01:09:21,478
You haven't stood still for an instant.

831
01:09:22,686 --> 01:09:25,814
May I say you ought to be following him,
not his wife.

832
01:09:25,923 --> 01:09:29,290
There's no point in screaming like that
at the birds, you know.

833
01:09:29,393 --> 01:09:32,294
They don't understand
you foreigners. Maniac.

834
01:09:32,496 --> 01:09:35,363
He thinks the birds
in Paris are foreigners.

835
01:09:36,467 --> 01:09:39,493
God damn it. <i>Dottore!</i>

836
01:09:40,170 --> 01:09:41,967
I do understand you.

837
01:09:42,473 --> 01:09:45,374
But the operation must be
quick and decisive.

838
01:09:56,920 --> 01:09:58,285
Third floor.

839
01:10:28,218 --> 01:10:30,448
You don't mind if we stay like this a bit?

840
01:10:30,554 --> 01:10:31,521
No.

841
01:10:31,622 --> 01:10:33,317
How silly you are.

842
01:10:33,424 --> 01:10:35,984
Remember what you yourself said
a while ago,

843
01:10:36,093 --> 01:10:38,152
"If I weren't married," you said.

844
01:10:38,262 --> 01:10:41,425
Yes, I might have said that.
I am married.

845
01:10:41,532 --> 01:10:43,466
It doesn't mean a thing.

846
01:10:44,968 --> 01:10:47,664
You have to understand
married to whom.

847
01:10:47,771 --> 01:10:49,102
I like him.

848
01:11:16,135 --> 01:11:17,659
Let's try on my new frock.

849
01:11:17,770 --> 01:11:21,399
No. Don't move. I want to dress you.

850
01:11:25,979 --> 01:11:29,881
How strange you are.
You want to be my maid now?

851
01:11:31,050 --> 01:11:34,076
What difference does it make?
It's my pleasure.

852
01:11:46,032 --> 01:11:48,762
Please, don't look at me.
I'm embarrassed.

853
01:11:48,868 --> 01:11:51,996
There's nothing wrong with it.
I'm a woman just as you are.

854
01:11:52,105 --> 01:11:55,268
Yes, but you look at me in a way...

855
01:11:55,375 --> 01:11:56,740
Turn around.

856
01:12:01,481 --> 01:12:03,415
How beautiful!

857
01:12:06,519 --> 01:12:08,919
How much I love Paris!

858
01:12:11,357 --> 01:12:13,188
When Marcello sees it!

859
01:12:34,347 --> 01:12:36,542
Violets? Violets, <i>monsieur?</i>

860
01:12:39,218 --> 01:12:40,947
Do you want violets?

861
01:12:41,621 --> 01:12:43,816
These are real Parma violets.

862
01:12:45,558 --> 01:12:47,719
- They're really from Parma?
- Absolutely.

863
01:12:47,827 --> 01:12:49,419
Let me have one.

864
01:12:50,930 --> 01:12:52,261
Thank you.

865
01:12:52,966 --> 01:12:54,934
"Ye prisoners of starvation!"

866
01:12:55,034 --> 01:12:58,026
<i>Arise ye prisoners of starvation</i>

867
01:12:58,137 --> 01:13:00,935
<i>Awake ye wretched of the Earth</i>

868
01:13:01,040 --> 01:13:04,441
<i>For justice thunders condemnation</i>

869
01:13:04,544 --> 01:13:07,877
<i>A better world in birth</i>

870
01:13:07,981 --> 01:13:11,644
<i>No more tradition's chains shall bind us</i>

871
01:13:11,751 --> 01:13:14,982
<i>Arise ye slaves no more in thrall</i>

872
01:13:15,088 --> 01:13:18,387
<i>The earth shall rise on new foundations</i>

873
01:13:18,491 --> 01:13:22,154
<i>We have been naught, we shall be all</i>

874
01:13:26,766 --> 01:13:30,224
<i>'Tis the final conflict</i>

875
01:13:30,336 --> 01:13:33,635
<i>Let each stand in his place</i>

876
01:13:33,740 --> 01:13:37,836
<i>The Internationale</i>

877
01:13:37,944 --> 01:13:41,505
<i>Shall lead the human race</i>

878
01:13:41,614 --> 01:13:45,482
<i>'Tis the final conflict</i>

879
01:13:45,585 --> 01:13:48,816
<i>Let each stand in his place</i>

880
01:13:48,921 --> 01:13:53,119
<i>The Internationale</i>

881
01:13:53,226 --> 01:13:56,093
<i>Shall lead the human race</i>

882
01:13:56,763 --> 01:13:57,923
Inside.

883
01:13:59,999 --> 01:14:01,990
- Come.
- What's the matter?

884
01:14:09,208 --> 01:14:12,575
- Do you like real Parma violets?
- They're not for me.

885
01:14:15,882 --> 01:14:17,816
I want you to have them.

886
01:14:18,317 --> 01:14:21,184
You couldn't have known
I'd be at the hotel.

887
01:14:21,721 --> 01:14:23,416
They're for Giulia.

888
01:14:24,724 --> 01:14:26,885
It's for you I bought them.

889
01:14:49,916 --> 01:14:51,781
Giulia will be beautiful tonight.

890
01:14:51,884 --> 01:14:54,079
Half past eight at the hotel.

891
01:14:59,725 --> 01:15:01,352
You know, I'm sad.

892
01:15:02,061 --> 01:15:05,519
Since we've arrived in Paris,
we haven't made love yet.

893
01:15:11,504 --> 01:15:15,565
Your knees are sharp.

894
01:15:30,123 --> 01:15:31,886
Here's news for you.

895
01:15:32,225 --> 01:15:34,750
The Quadris have a house
in the Savoie.

896
01:15:35,094 --> 01:15:37,426
Anna says the Professor leaves
tomorrow morning by car

897
01:15:37,530 --> 01:15:39,020
while she stays here.

898
01:15:39,132 --> 01:15:41,965
Only for a day or so, then she's
planning to join her husband

899
01:15:42,068 --> 01:15:45,060
and wants us to visit with them
in the mountains.

900
01:15:45,171 --> 01:15:46,866
I have the address.

901
01:15:49,475 --> 01:15:51,443
Nice, don't you think so?

902
01:15:58,251 --> 01:16:00,845
She told me they have
enormous beds in their villa

903
01:16:00,953 --> 01:16:03,387
which make awful noises!

904
01:16:06,492 --> 01:16:09,120
And she says there are big,
big forests in the neighborhood

905
01:16:09,228 --> 01:16:11,219
where no one ever passes.

906
01:16:17,403 --> 01:16:19,166
Anna says...

907
01:16:19,605 --> 01:16:22,665
Anna told me you can even
make love in the snow.

908
01:16:25,811 --> 01:16:29,907
Can you imagine the Professor
wandering around in the woods naked?

909
01:16:30,483 --> 01:16:33,748
You had me convinced
you were the typical new Italian.

910
01:16:33,853 --> 01:16:36,185
No such type exists yet,
but we're creating him.

911
01:16:36,289 --> 01:16:39,087
- Through repression?
- No, through example.

912
01:16:39,458 --> 01:16:42,950
Giving him castor oil?
Throwing him into prison?

913
01:16:43,529 --> 01:16:45,292
By torturing them? Blackmailing?

914
01:16:45,398 --> 01:16:48,492
Anna. Please, dear, calm down.

915
01:16:50,169 --> 01:16:53,002
Clerici is a Fascist. I'm an Anti-Fascist.

916
01:16:54,073 --> 01:16:55,506
We both knew.

917
01:16:56,075 --> 01:16:58,009
And we decided to have supper
together all the same.

918
01:16:58,110 --> 01:17:01,136
- And get the wives drunk.
- The old Professor and his ex-pupil.

919
01:17:01,247 --> 01:17:05,518
- Giulia, what's the matter?
- And yet I'm willing to bet.

920
01:17:05,518 --> 01:17:05,813
- Giulia, what's the matter?
- And yet I'm willing to bet.

921
01:17:05,918 --> 01:17:07,317
God, I've drunk so much!

922
01:17:07,420 --> 01:17:10,947
- You may change your mind yet.
- Impossible, Professor.

923
01:17:11,791 --> 01:17:14,817
My husband is naive about these things.

924
01:17:15,695 --> 01:17:19,153
I can't forget that Clerici was
one of my best students ever.

925
01:17:19,265 --> 01:17:23,326
Really? Tell me.
What was Marcello like as a student?

926
01:17:23,436 --> 01:17:26,701
- Serious. Too serious.
- But you can't be too serious.

927
01:17:26,806 --> 01:17:28,740
Really serious people are never serious.

928
01:17:28,841 --> 01:17:32,038
Giulia, did you ever see
your husband laugh?

929
01:17:32,144 --> 01:17:34,874
No, but then, he's a very serious man.
That's his nature.

930
01:17:34,981 --> 01:17:37,347
- Nothing the matter with that.
- That's not my nature at all.

931
01:17:37,450 --> 01:17:40,044
I've an idea, Clerici.
You should both remain here.

932
01:17:40,152 --> 01:17:43,246
You will understand a great deal
about many things living here.

933
01:17:43,356 --> 01:17:45,984
For you, it's an important opportunity.

934
01:17:46,726 --> 01:17:48,819
What do you know, Professor?

935
01:17:49,028 --> 01:17:50,188
He's right.

936
01:17:50,296 --> 01:17:53,060
He's only in Paris
to enjoy his honeymoon.

937
01:17:53,165 --> 01:17:55,133
By the way,
did Giulia mention my idea to you?

938
01:17:55,234 --> 01:17:57,896
- We have a lovely guest room...
- With an enormous bed!

939
01:17:58,004 --> 01:18:00,472
And from la Savoie
you can go back to Italy.

940
01:18:00,573 --> 01:18:03,007
Thank you,
but I promised Giulia to show her Paris.

941
01:18:03,109 --> 01:18:04,804
I'm half-drunk already!

942
01:18:04,910 --> 01:18:07,378
That's splendid.
My husband will leave tomorrow.

943
01:18:07,480 --> 01:18:10,847
And after you see some more of Paris,
we'll join him.

944
01:18:14,620 --> 01:18:17,180
Marcello, tell the truth.
Would you like us to go?

945
01:18:17,290 --> 01:18:20,282
But of course I would.
They're really so kind.

946
01:18:20,860 --> 01:18:24,023
- Well, all right.
- Perhaps Giulia doesn't want to go.

947
01:18:24,130 --> 01:18:25,188
No, no!

948
01:18:25,298 --> 01:18:27,766
If you don't like me, you can just say so.

949
01:18:28,734 --> 01:18:30,861
Don't embarrass dear Giulia.

950
01:18:32,238 --> 01:18:35,435
- We'll definitely come. Right, Giulia?
- Yes.

951
01:18:36,909 --> 01:18:38,501
Let me sit there.

952
01:18:44,317 --> 01:18:47,013
God, it's going around, the whole place.

953
01:18:48,120 --> 01:18:51,317
It's like that restaurant
we had on the train

954
01:18:54,493 --> 01:18:56,620
with that funny fat man.

955
01:19:06,005 --> 01:19:09,497
Marcello, will you give me
a proof of your friendship?

956
01:19:10,843 --> 01:19:14,006
There's something to be sent. A letter.

957
01:19:15,014 --> 01:19:18,916
To Rome. To a comrade.
I ask you to help me.

958
01:19:19,885 --> 01:19:22,615
It has to be delivered personally.
There's no hurry.

959
01:19:22,722 --> 01:19:24,952
When you get back to Italy
from our place.

960
01:19:25,057 --> 01:19:26,922
This might mean prison.

961
01:19:27,026 --> 01:19:29,187
Any one of my men
would risk much more.

962
01:19:29,295 --> 01:19:31,388
Professor, one would say
you're doing this purposely,

963
01:19:31,497 --> 01:19:33,897
just to get me into trouble there.

964
01:19:34,800 --> 01:19:36,995
Considering what you're
going back to, Clerici,

965
01:19:37,103 --> 01:19:40,470
- a month in a Fascist jail may be better.
- Excuse me.

966
01:19:54,687 --> 01:19:56,018
What is it?

967
01:19:57,757 --> 01:19:59,384
What's the matter?

968
01:20:01,193 --> 01:20:03,127
Hey, <i>Dottore!</i> Watch out!

969
01:20:04,864 --> 01:20:08,300
What? I'm here to protect you
and you want to kill me?

970
01:20:09,268 --> 01:20:13,500
I don't want to kill anyone. Here.
I don't want to carry it anymore.

971
01:20:15,641 --> 01:20:17,506
What is this all about?

972
01:20:18,711 --> 01:20:22,203
- You giving up?
- No, it's so clumsy.

973
01:20:23,616 --> 01:20:27,347
I don't even know how to use it.
It's in my way, it's so heavy.

974
01:20:33,993 --> 01:20:37,588
Listen to me, comrade!

975
01:20:38,397 --> 01:20:40,865
I want you to look straight at me.

976
01:20:41,233 --> 01:20:44,794
We're in a war, right?
You give up, you're a deserter.

977
01:20:47,706 --> 01:20:50,539
Everybody's thought
of deserting at least once.

978
01:20:50,643 --> 01:20:54,443
- I wouldn't think of that.
- Even I did. Really. Yes, yes, yes.

979
01:20:55,080 --> 01:20:59,380
But I said to myself, " Manganiello,
why, what are you thinking of?"

980
01:20:59,485 --> 01:21:01,476
It isn't your patriotism,

981
01:21:01,687 --> 01:21:04,315
it isn't your honor you are betraying.

982
01:21:05,057 --> 01:21:06,649
It is really you.

983
01:21:07,893 --> 01:21:09,451
After a while,

984
01:21:10,329 --> 01:21:13,856
I managed a hearty pat on my back,
smoked another cigar,

985
01:21:14,266 --> 01:21:17,724
and what did I think? " Let's go.

986
01:21:19,071 --> 01:21:20,595
"Courage now.

987
01:21:22,141 --> 01:21:24,041
"Comrade Manganiello?"

988
01:21:24,877 --> 01:21:26,572
Fight or be beaten.

989
01:21:27,813 --> 01:21:29,280
It's freezing!

990
01:21:29,982 --> 01:21:32,109
Hurry. We're going to dance.

991
01:21:32,885 --> 01:21:34,648
You'll make me fall!

992
01:22:14,226 --> 01:22:15,420
Come on.

993
01:22:23,969 --> 01:22:25,061
Thanks.

994
01:22:25,170 --> 01:22:26,569
If you were what you say,

995
01:22:26,672 --> 01:22:28,970
you would have agreed
to carry that letter

996
01:22:29,074 --> 01:22:32,510
and you would have used it
against our friends in Rome.

997
01:22:39,451 --> 01:22:42,420
Well, take a look.
There's nothing written.

998
01:22:43,989 --> 01:22:46,822
I thought it best to put you to the test.

999
01:23:21,827 --> 01:23:23,954
They must stop dancing.

1000
01:23:24,363 --> 01:23:25,557
But why?

1001
01:23:27,199 --> 01:23:29,064
They're both so pretty.

1002
01:23:45,384 --> 01:23:47,750
Well, what's there to stare at?

1003
01:23:47,853 --> 01:23:52,449
This is Paris,
and I'm a fashionable woman, aren't I?

1004
01:23:52,558 --> 01:23:55,652
- You're crazy, completely.
- All right. Let's dance!

1005
01:23:55,761 --> 01:23:58,093
Everyone! All of you!

1006
01:23:58,731 --> 01:24:02,633
Everybody, come on!

1007
01:25:07,800 --> 01:25:10,268
- Tomorrow by car at dawn.
- Wait!

1008
01:25:10,369 --> 01:25:12,929
- What about his wife?
- She doesn't go.

1009
01:25:14,106 --> 01:25:15,801
Better without her.

1010
01:25:16,308 --> 01:25:18,003
We'll meet in Rome!

1011
01:25:18,844 --> 01:25:20,937
And the best of luck to you!

1012
01:26:24,209 --> 01:26:27,508
Who knows what
you think of me, Professor?

1013
01:26:27,613 --> 01:26:29,706
I've had too much champagne!

1014
01:26:31,583 --> 01:26:34,108
It's good for anybody
to get drunk once in a while.

1015
01:26:34,219 --> 01:26:35,914
You won't believe this.

1016
01:26:36,021 --> 01:26:38,717
You upset me like
you're giving me an exam.

1017
01:26:38,824 --> 01:26:41,622
If you're prepared, everybody'll pass?

1018
01:26:54,640 --> 01:26:58,235
Listen. I'll be going tomorrow
with my husband.

1019
01:26:59,077 --> 01:27:00,635
You must remain.

1020
01:27:05,617 --> 01:27:08,108
Please remain in town. Do it for me.

1021
01:27:08,387 --> 01:27:10,480
Didn't you decide to go
with Giulia and me?

1022
01:27:10,589 --> 01:27:13,524
Haven't you observed
she can't stand me, your Giulia?

1023
01:27:14,059 --> 01:27:15,083
Pardon!

1024
01:27:15,194 --> 01:27:17,822
But Giulia's so stupid.
Can't you see she's drunk?

1025
01:27:17,930 --> 01:27:20,296
We've all lost our heads a little tonight.

1026
01:27:20,399 --> 01:27:23,493
Besides, you're mistaken
to say she can't bear you.

1027
01:27:23,602 --> 01:27:26,969
She mentioned that she admires you.

1028
01:27:28,841 --> 01:27:33,972
- What else did she say?
- That she finds you seductive.

1029
01:27:35,814 --> 01:27:37,441
I changed my mind.

1030
01:27:38,750 --> 01:27:44,052
I'll stay with you in Paris. Glad?

1031
01:27:44,456 --> 01:27:47,391
Anna! The Professor
is propositioning me!

1032
01:27:47,693 --> 01:27:48,887
Help!

1033
01:27:48,994 --> 01:27:53,522
I feel so happy that in a minute
I know I'm going to feel terrible!

1034
01:27:54,099 --> 01:27:55,361
<i>Ciao!</i>

1035
01:28:20,325 --> 01:28:24,386
Damn. I'm beginning to get tired.

1036
01:28:39,745 --> 01:28:41,872
- Manganiello.
- Yes, <i>Dottore.</i>

1037
01:28:43,048 --> 01:28:45,846
- I've just had a fantastic dream.
- You did?

1038
01:28:46,418 --> 01:28:48,215
I was in Switzerland.

1039
01:28:48,320 --> 01:28:50,550
And you were taking me
for an operation in a hospital

1040
01:28:50,656 --> 01:28:51,850
because I was blind.

1041
01:28:51,957 --> 01:28:54,084
Switzerland. It's beautiful.

1042
01:28:54,393 --> 01:28:56,725
And Professor Quadri did the operation.

1043
01:28:57,262 --> 01:29:00,720
The operation was a success
and I was leaving soon

1044
01:29:01,433 --> 01:29:04,596
with the wife of the Professor.
And she loved me.

1045
01:29:08,907 --> 01:29:10,306
Switzerland.

1046
01:29:10,676 --> 01:29:12,541
I remember in Milan

1047
01:29:12,644 --> 01:29:14,942
when I was a child,
we used to sing a song.

1048
01:29:15,047 --> 01:29:16,378
Wait a minute.

1049
01:29:40,172 --> 01:29:42,436
In Africa after all that work
and four dead men,

1050
01:29:42,541 --> 01:29:45,237
we discovered
it was no longer necessary.

1051
01:29:45,944 --> 01:29:49,607
And my superior,
"You have ruined us all!

1052
01:29:49,715 --> 01:29:51,808
"You're only beasts, you are!"

1053
01:29:51,917 --> 01:29:55,353
"Now wait a second," I said.
"We are men, not beasts."

1054
01:30:00,959 --> 01:30:02,859
That woman should have
returned to her bed

1055
01:30:02,961 --> 01:30:04,929
and stayed there all day.

1056
01:30:08,266 --> 01:30:09,563
God!

1057
01:30:09,668 --> 01:30:12,933
- Love can certainly...
- What are you trying to say?

1058
01:30:15,040 --> 01:30:17,008
No. Nothing, <i>Dottore.</i>

1059
01:30:17,576 --> 01:30:21,603
No. I was saying that sometimes
love can even perform miracles.

1060
01:30:33,191 --> 01:30:34,317
There!

1061
01:30:36,528 --> 01:30:38,291
It's them, isn't it?

1062
01:30:39,998 --> 01:30:41,966
Keep about 60 feet back.

1063
01:30:59,184 --> 01:31:00,446
There's a car behind us.

1064
01:31:00,552 --> 01:31:01,917
- So?
- Following us.

1065
01:31:02,020 --> 01:31:04,955
Nothing the matter with that.
Why are you so nervous?

1066
01:31:15,967 --> 01:31:17,264
Watch out!

1067
01:31:32,451 --> 01:31:34,646
Must be something the matter.

1068
01:31:34,753 --> 01:31:36,880
Don't get out, please, I beg you!

1069
01:31:36,988 --> 01:31:40,185
- Well, why not?
- I don't know, but I'm frightened.

1070
01:32:27,405 --> 01:32:29,839
We can't just sit here like this.

1071
01:32:29,941 --> 01:32:31,670
I'll be right back.

1072
01:32:32,644 --> 01:32:33,941
Wait here.

1073
01:32:36,615 --> 01:32:37,673
Luca!

1074
01:33:21,826 --> 01:33:23,521
I thought you were ill.

1075
01:33:23,628 --> 01:33:26,222
What is it? What do you want from me?

1076
01:34:58,523 --> 01:35:00,388
Look out, I'm shooting.

1077
01:35:37,128 --> 01:35:40,063
How disgusting. I've always said so.

1078
01:35:40,165 --> 01:35:43,896
Make me work in the shit,
sure, but not with a coward.

1079
01:35:44,002 --> 01:35:46,664
If it's up to me, cowards,
homosexuals and Jews,

1080
01:35:46,771 --> 01:35:48,170
they're all the same thing.

1081
01:35:49,908 --> 01:35:53,344
If it were up to me,
I'd stand them all against a wall.

1082
01:35:56,815 --> 01:36:01,343
Better yet,
eliminate them when they're born.

1083
01:37:38,349 --> 01:37:39,646
<i>Attention.</i>

1084
01:37:41,653 --> 01:37:43,052
<i>Attention.</i>

1085
01:37:44,522 --> 01:37:48,219
<i>His Majesty King Vittorio Emanuele</i>

1086
01:37:48,326 --> 01:37:53,093
<i>accepted the resignation</i>
<i>of His Excellency Benito Mussolini</i>

1087
01:37:53,431 --> 01:37:57,424
<i>as head of the government,</i>
<i>Prime Minister and Secretary of State.</i>

1088
01:37:57,969 --> 01:37:59,732
<i>His Majesty has named as</i>
<i>head of the government,</i>

1089
01:37:59,838 --> 01:38:02,238
<i>Prime Minister and Secretary of State,</i>

1090
01:38:02,340 --> 01:38:06,743
<i>His Excellency Marshal Pietro Badoglio.</i>

1091
01:38:19,224 --> 01:38:22,352
How elegant you are
with your mama's hat on!

1092
01:38:26,197 --> 01:38:28,722
You even put on the foxes
Mama brought from Paris.

1093
01:38:28,833 --> 01:38:30,232
Good for Marta!

1094
01:38:30,335 --> 01:38:33,793
<i>King Vittorio Emanuele has</i>
<i>accepted the resignation</i>

1095
01:38:33,905 --> 01:38:37,602
<i>of His Excellency Benito Mussolini</i>

1096
01:38:38,009 --> 01:38:42,036
<i>as head of the government,</i>
<i>Prime minister and Secretary of State,</i>

1097
01:38:42,580 --> 01:38:45,048
<i>and His Majesty has named as</i>
<i>head of the government,</i>

1098
01:38:45,149 --> 01:38:48,084
<i>Prime minister and Secretary of State,</i>

1099
01:38:48,186 --> 01:38:51,485
<i>His Excellency Marshal Pietro Badoglio.</i>

1100
01:39:17,081 --> 01:39:18,742
A red apple.

1101
01:39:22,353 --> 01:39:25,652
Ready? Hail Mary, full of grace...

1102
01:39:25,757 --> 01:39:27,850
"Hail Mary, full of grace..."

1103
01:39:27,959 --> 01:39:31,019
- the Lord is with Thee.
- "The Lord is with Thee."

1104
01:39:31,129 --> 01:39:35,759
- Blessed art Thou amongst women...
- "Blessed art Thou amongst women..."

1105
01:39:36,467 --> 01:39:39,630
...and blessed is the fruit
of Thy womb, Jesus.

1106
01:39:41,239 --> 01:39:43,707
"...the fruit of Thy womb, Jesus."

1107
01:39:44,776 --> 01:39:46,869
Holy Mary, Mother of God...

1108
01:39:47,979 --> 01:39:50,209
"Holy Mary, Mother of God..."

1109
01:39:50,315 --> 01:39:52,840
...pray for us sinners...

1110
01:39:52,951 --> 01:39:55,112
"...pray for us sinners..."

1111
01:39:55,219 --> 01:39:59,883
...now and at the hour of our death.
- "...now and at the hour of our death."

1112
01:39:59,991 --> 01:40:01,219
Italo called.

1113
01:40:01,326 --> 01:40:03,658
- Amen.
- "Amen."

1114
01:40:05,363 --> 01:40:08,355
Now to sleep.
Come on, lie down and sleep.

1115
01:40:12,537 --> 01:40:15,938
- Italo?
- Yes. Italo.

1116
01:40:20,612 --> 01:40:24,241
- What did he want?
- He'll expect you at the usual place.

1117
01:40:27,885 --> 01:40:30,683
<i>Italo. After all this time.</i>

1118
01:40:38,696 --> 01:40:40,687
How awful they all are!

1119
01:40:41,366 --> 01:40:43,994
Celebrating because
the King threw out Mussolini,

1120
01:40:44,102 --> 01:40:46,593
when yesterday they were all for him.

1121
01:40:46,704 --> 01:40:48,934
I can't wait till we get them out of here.

1122
01:40:49,040 --> 01:40:51,565
Why see Italo? What's the use of it?

1123
01:40:52,410 --> 01:40:55,573
If he called it means he needs me,
and I'm going.

1124
01:40:57,482 --> 01:41:00,212
I was always the one
who took him around.

1125
01:41:00,818 --> 01:41:02,649
I took him everywhere.

1126
01:41:03,921 --> 01:41:06,890
He used to say that
when I described things to him

1127
01:41:06,991 --> 01:41:09,755
it was like seeing them
with his own eyes.

1128
01:41:10,895 --> 01:41:12,294
Go to sleep.

1129
01:41:14,298 --> 01:41:16,027
Marcello, you've got to take care,
you hear?

1130
01:41:16,134 --> 01:41:17,158
Why?

1131
01:41:18,102 --> 01:41:19,694
What do you mean?

1132
01:41:22,040 --> 01:41:23,234
Nothing.

1133
01:41:26,644 --> 01:41:30,136
Wait, listen.
What are you going to do now?

1134
01:41:30,248 --> 01:41:33,046
The same as everyone else
who thought like me.

1135
01:41:35,086 --> 01:41:37,520
When there are so many of us,
there's no risk.

1136
01:41:37,622 --> 01:41:40,955
I know, but I want to say
the business with Quadri...

1137
01:41:53,571 --> 01:41:56,267
I don't know what you're talking about.

1138
01:41:59,544 --> 01:42:01,637
In Paris, Anna,

1139
01:42:02,980 --> 01:42:05,676
maybe in order
to get me away from you,

1140
01:42:06,217 --> 01:42:08,913
told me you worked
for the secret police.

1141
01:42:11,289 --> 01:42:15,123
- And you? What did you answer?
- That it wasn't important.

1142
01:42:15,493 --> 01:42:18,087
That I was your wife and I loved you.

1143
01:42:19,330 --> 01:42:22,493
And if you worked for them,
it was your decision.

1144
01:42:26,404 --> 01:42:30,602
But then, when the Quadris were killed,

1145
01:42:30,708 --> 01:42:34,235
how scared I became.

1146
01:42:42,253 --> 01:42:44,551
And what do you think of it now?

1147
01:42:49,460 --> 01:42:51,792
Well, I think that, after all,

1148
01:42:54,465 --> 01:42:57,195
it was an important step in your career.

1149
01:42:58,102 --> 01:42:59,535
That's right.

1150
01:43:02,440 --> 01:43:04,305
Marcello, don't go out!

1151
01:43:08,880 --> 01:43:10,643
They could hurt you.

1152
01:43:10,848 --> 01:43:12,748
I won't be in danger.

1153
01:43:13,918 --> 01:43:16,546
After all, what have I done? My duty.

1154
01:43:17,221 --> 01:43:19,212
But why do you want to go?

1155
01:43:21,125 --> 01:43:23,855
I want to see how a dictatorship falls.

1156
01:43:36,340 --> 01:43:39,798
Mama! Where are you? I'm afraid.

1157
01:43:41,913 --> 01:43:44,108
I'm here, darling. I'm coming.

1158
01:44:01,399 --> 01:44:02,627
Marcello?

1159
01:44:08,339 --> 01:44:11,240
There's something
that's still stuck to you.

1160
01:44:12,777 --> 01:44:14,677
- Where?
- Here.

1161
01:44:15,680 --> 01:44:16,908
Oh, yes.

1162
01:44:57,388 --> 01:44:58,753
What about eating?

1163
01:44:58,856 --> 01:45:01,381
As long as there are cats around,
I manage.

1164
01:45:01,492 --> 01:45:04,154
They say cat meat tastes like rabbit.

1165
01:45:04,262 --> 01:45:06,196
Too bad we didn't meet yesterday.

1166
01:45:06,297 --> 01:45:08,356
I had a whipped cream cake at home.

1167
01:45:08,466 --> 01:45:10,593
- With real cream?
- Yes, why not?

1168
01:45:10,701 --> 01:45:13,261
- You need eggs for that.
- Somebody I met lives in the country.

1169
01:45:13,371 --> 01:45:14,963
He sends me bread, too.

1170
01:45:15,072 --> 01:45:17,336
Fresh eggs? Bread?

1171
01:45:17,441 --> 01:45:20,308
He keeps me supplied.
I never lack for anything in my house.

1172
01:45:20,411 --> 01:45:22,777
Chickens, butter, fresh cheese.

1173
01:45:22,880 --> 01:45:25,508
- And potatoes?
- Potatoes, too.

1174
01:45:25,616 --> 01:45:28,107
If you come home with me,
I'll be happy to make you an omelet.

1175
01:45:28,219 --> 01:45:30,312
- What kind?
- A jelly omelet.

1176
01:45:30,755 --> 01:45:32,518
You must be tired
of eating cats all the time.

1177
01:45:32,623 --> 01:45:36,218
Yes. I ate too many of them.
And they're not so easy to find.

1178
01:45:36,327 --> 01:45:39,057
- What did you do?
- Ate mice.

1179
01:45:39,163 --> 01:45:40,824
There are more rats with the cats gone?

1180
01:45:40,932 --> 01:45:42,900
Yes, but they're all skin and bones.

1181
01:45:43,000 --> 01:45:44,399
Listen. I don't live far from here.

1182
01:45:44,502 --> 01:45:47,096
Why don't you come
and have dinner with me?

1183
01:45:47,538 --> 01:45:49,665
- Is there a place to sleep?
- You can stay.

1184
01:45:49,774 --> 01:45:52,766
Nice shoes you have. Soft.

1185
01:45:53,144 --> 01:45:54,475
They were a present.

1186
01:45:54,578 --> 01:45:57,206
I got a present, too. A Siamese cat.

1187
01:45:57,315 --> 01:45:59,283
- Was he good?
- Too tough.

1188
01:46:00,217 --> 01:46:02,777
I have a pair of suede shoes.
You can have them.

1189
01:46:02,887 --> 01:46:06,618
And I have a nice oriental kimono.
Like Madame Butterfly's.

1190
01:46:06,757 --> 01:46:08,486
You know who Madame Butterfly is?

1191
01:46:08,592 --> 01:46:09,650
Lino!

1192
01:46:10,494 --> 01:46:14,692
- Is your name Lino? You!
- Me? Why?

1193
01:46:15,967 --> 01:46:18,595
You were a chauffeur, right?

1194
01:46:19,103 --> 01:46:22,698
- But a long time ago.
- Yes.

1195
01:46:27,311 --> 01:46:32,146
- You had a pistol.
- I? I don't understand you.

1196
01:46:33,684 --> 01:46:35,549
And you're alive still.

1197
01:46:36,187 --> 01:46:38,587
But I don't know you.
What do you want of me?

1198
01:46:38,689 --> 01:46:40,316
What's that scar?

1199
01:46:41,092 --> 01:46:43,185
- There was an accident.
- What accident?

1200
01:46:43,294 --> 01:46:44,818
What do you want?
Take your hands off me!

1201
01:46:44,929 --> 01:46:46,191
Where were you?

1202
01:46:46,297 --> 01:46:48,891
What were you doing
on March 25, 1917?

1203
01:46:49,333 --> 01:46:51,767
Me? I... Who are you?
You must be crazy.

1204
01:46:51,869 --> 01:46:54,667
What were you doing
on March 25, 1917?

1205
01:46:54,772 --> 01:46:56,171
Let me alone!

1206
01:46:56,273 --> 01:46:58,434
And the 15th of October, 1938.

1207
01:46:58,542 --> 01:47:00,669
Where were you?
What were you doing?

1208
01:47:01,479 --> 01:47:05,745
What were you doing at 4:00 p.m.
On October 15th, 1938?

1209
01:47:05,850 --> 01:47:07,841
Where were you?
What were you doing?

1210
01:47:07,952 --> 01:47:11,388
What were you doing? I've got to know.

1211
01:47:12,957 --> 01:47:16,188
Murderer! Murderer!

1212
01:47:18,329 --> 01:47:22,095
He killed a man, a political exile,

1213
01:47:22,933 --> 01:47:25,925
on October 15th, 1938!

1214
01:47:26,303 --> 01:47:28,168
Yes, Professor Quadri!

1215
01:47:28,506 --> 01:47:29,905
Luca Quadri!

1216
01:47:30,674 --> 01:47:33,404
And his wife Anna Quadri.

1217
01:47:36,781 --> 01:47:39,807
He's a homosexual, a Fascist!

1218
01:47:40,484 --> 01:47:42,577
And his name is Pasqualino!

1219
01:47:44,288 --> 01:47:45,619
Semirama!

1220
01:47:46,524 --> 01:47:48,583
Pasqualino Semirama!

1221
01:47:48,859 --> 01:47:53,125
Marcello, don't do that.

1222
01:47:56,100 --> 01:47:58,068
Marcello, where are you?

1223
01:47:59,336 --> 01:48:01,702
- Fascist!
- No, Marcello!

1224
01:48:01,806 --> 01:48:04,934
He, too, is a Fascist. Right here.

1225
01:48:05,042 --> 01:48:06,907
- What are you doing this for?
- This one's a Fascist.

1226
01:48:07,011 --> 01:48:10,777
Marcello, no. No, Marcello, please.

1227
01:48:10,881 --> 01:48:12,940
Marcello, no, no, Marcello!

1228
01:48:13,984 --> 01:48:17,010
Italo Montanari! Fascist!

1229
01:48:17,121 --> 01:48:18,952
